<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-12889] log clean group consider empty log segment to avoid empty log left</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12889</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;to avoid log index 4 byte relative offset overflow, log cleaner group check log segments offset to make sure group offset range not exceed Int.MaxValue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this offset check currentlly not cosider next is next log segment is empty, so there will left empty log files every about 2^31 messages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the left empty logs will be reprocessed every clean cycle, which will rewrite it with same empty content, witch cause little no need io.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for __consumer_offsets topic, normally we can set&#160;cleanup.policy to&#160;compact,delete to get rid of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;my cluster is 0.10.1.1, but after aylize trunk code, it should has same problem too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;some of my left empty logs,(run ls -l)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Dec 16 2017 00000000000000000000.index&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Dec 16 2017 00000000000000000000.log&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Dec 16 2017 00000000000000000000.timeindex&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 15 2018 00000000002148249632.index&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 15 2018 00000000002148249632.log&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 15 2018 00000000002148249632.timeindex&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 27 2018 00000000004295766494.index&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 27 2018 00000000004295766494.log&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-r&lt;/del&gt;---- 1 u g 0 Jan&#160; 27 2018 00000000004295766494.timeindex&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
